SWIG has limited support for parsing complex [default arguments](https://www.swig.org/Doc1.3/SWIG.html#SWIG_default_args)]. One solution is to simplify the default argument in the SWIG interface file, or provide an overloaded version of the constructor without the default argument for SWIG to wrap.

